    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-01-24T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-01-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="77"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.85/74: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Collier</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-24T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1928—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. Parliamentary Tariff Commission has included in proposed tariff law provision
                    to rebate duties [on] certain articles arriving Chile in Chilean vessels (see my
                    telegram of November 9, 5 p.m., 172<note n="2" xml:id="d77fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1927v01#pg_535">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., p. 535</ref>.</note>), but as result of my
                    representations Minister of Hacienda has asked President of Senate in the name
                    of Government to suppress this article.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Collier</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
